N2  - Managers of research and development (R otherwise R&D search continues. One interesting property of RTL is that it is strictly less than the highest possible technology level. Thus the economic limit of R&D (RTL) differs from the technological limit of R&D. Ex ante, an R&D program manager should not press for the technological limit of R&D once the current technology level exceeds or equals RTL. However, ex post, one may end up with a technology level greater than RTL. Moreover, R&D search may be resumed in an abandoned R&D area if (i) interest rate declines, (ii) R&D quasi-fixed cost reduces, or (iii) basic research provides a favorable shape-preserving shift of the distribution of technological opportunities.
