TY  - JOUR
T1  - Algorithmic Solution of Some Queues with Overflows
AU  - Neuts, Marcel F.
AU  - Kumar, Seshavadhani
Y1  - 1982/08/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.28.8.925
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.28.8.925
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 925
EP  - 935
VL  - 28
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The overflow stream from an M/PH/1 queue of finite capacity is used as the input to an unbounded queue with one or more exponential servers. It is shown that the combined system, consisting of the two queues, may be studied as a highly structured Markov process. In the stable case, this Markov process has a matrix-geometric invariant vector. Particular features of the infinitesimal generator of the process may be used to simplify the numerical computation of various steady-state features of the model. Several variants and numerical examples are discussed.
AB  - The overflow stream from an M/PH/1 queue of finite capacity is used as the input to an unbounded queue with one or more exponential servers. It is shown that the combined system, consisting of the two queues, may be studied as a highly structured Markov process. In the stable case, this Markov process has a matrix-geometric invariant vector. Particular features of the infinitesimal generator of the process may be used to simplify the numerical computation of various steady-state features of the model. Several variants and numerical examples are discussed.
